# English-only output (mandatory)

**Regardless of the user's input language (including Portuguese), all project artifacts must be written in English.**

## Applies to

- Source code (variables, functions, classes, types, enums)
- Comments and docstrings
- Test names and descriptions
- Commit messages and PR titles/descriptions
- Documentation (`docs/`, README, ADRs)
- Error messages exposed to developers/operators
- Log message keys and structured log field names
- API route paths, query params, and JSON field names
- Database table/column names and migration descriptions
- Configuration keys and environment variable names

## Rules

- User may write prompts in any language; agent output in code/docs **must be English**.
- Domain terms use English Ubiquitous Language (`PurchaseOrder`, not `PedidoCompra`).
- User-facing product copy (UI strings for end users) may be localized separately via i18n — default locale files still use English keys.
- Do not mix languages in the same file.

## Examples

```typescript
// BAD — Portuguese in code
function calcularTotalPedido(itens: Item[]) { /* soma os valores */ }

// GOOD — English only
function calculateOrderTotal(items: OrderItem[]) { /* sums line amounts */ }
```
